text: Doris Posch (born 1 April 1973) is a track and road cyclist from Austria. She represented her nation at the 2001 and 2002 UCI Road World Championships. She has won the Austrian National Time Trial Championships six times. ==References== ==External links== * profile at Procyclingstats.com Category:1973 births Category:Austrian female cyclists Category:Living people Category:People from Imst District Category:Sportspeople from Tyrol (state)
